---
title: API Request/Response Flow
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant F as Frontend
    participant API as Backend API
    participant DB as SQLite Cache

    Note over F,DB: Health Check Flow
    F->>+API: GET /api/health
    API->>API: resolve projects_path
    API-->>-F: {status, projects_path}

    Note over F,DB: Summary Data Flow
    F->>+API: GET /api/summary
    API->>+DB: SUM over agg (granularity='daily')
    DB-->>-API: Aggregate usage data
    API-->>-F: [{cost, tokens, sessions}]

    Note over F,DB: Time-Based Analytics
    F->>+API: GET /api/usage/daily
    API->>+DB: SELECT from agg WHERE granularity='daily'
    DB-->>-API: Daily breakdown
    API-->>-F: [{date, cost, tokens}]

    F->>+API: GET /api/usage/weekly
    API->>+DB: SELECT from agg WHERE granularity='weekly'
    DB-->>-API: Weekly breakdown
    API-->>-F: [{week, cost, sessions}]

    F->>+API: GET /api/usage/monthly
    API->>+DB: SELECT from agg WHERE granularity='monthly'
    DB-->>-API: Monthly breakdown
    API-->>-F: [{month, cost, events}]

    F->>+API: GET /api/usage/hourly
    API->>+DB: SELECT from agg WHERE granularity='hourly'
    DB-->>-API: Hourly breakdown
    API-->>-F: [{hour, cost, events}]

    Note over F,DB: Session & Project Data
    F->>+API: GET /api/sessions
    API->>+DB: SELECT from sessions
    DB-->>-API: Session details
    API-->>-F: [{session_id, cost}]

    F->>+API: GET /api/projects
    API->>+DB: SELECT project_id, aggregates FROM sessions
    DB-->>-API: Per-project aggregates
    API-->>-F: [{project_id, total_cost}]

    F->>+API: GET /api/usage/top-projects-weekly
    API->>+DB: Two-stage query on agg (weekly)
    DB-->>-API: Top 3 projects (8 weeks)
    API-->>-F: [{project_id, week, cost}]

    Note over F,DB: Call Analytics (event_calls fact table)
    F->>+API: GET /api/calls/timeline
    API->>+DB: GROUP BY time_bucket, call_type<br/>FROM event_calls
    DB-->>-API: Call counts per (bucket, type)
    API-->>-F: [{time_bucket, call_type, call_count}]

    F->>+API: GET /api/calls/top
    API->>+DB: TOP-N over event_calls<br/>WHERE call_type=?
    DB-->>-API: Top-N call names
    API-->>-F: [{call_name, call_count, session_count}]
